1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,000
=Episode 8=

16
00:01:46,850 --> 00:01:49,051
I've always known that Lysen
has a genius.

17
00:01:49,210 --> 00:01:51,090
She helped Jiang Dongchao out twice.

18
00:01:52,051 --> 00:01:55,210
Now that I've met you in person,
you really do look like

19
00:01:55,210 --> 00:01:55,930
the Little Genius

20
00:01:55,930 --> 00:01:57,010
I imagined.

21
00:01:58,411 --> 00:01:59,210
Don't worry.

22
00:01:59,850 --> 00:02:01,891
Jiang Dongchao won't find out we've met.

23
00:02:02,171 --> 00:02:03,090
I'm not worried.

24
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:05,531
Mr. Pengyu, don't you also

25
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:07,010
keep your plan

26
00:02:07,010 --> 00:02:08,090
under wraps?

27
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:09,850
What do you mean?

28
00:02:12,287 --> 00:02:14,610
The feud between the Xian family
and Jiang Dongchao

29
00:02:14,610 --> 00:02:15,811
isn't hard to trace.

30
00:02:17,770 --> 00:02:18,570
If you think

31
00:02:18,570 --> 00:02:20,010
I'm a genius,

32
00:02:21,131 --> 00:02:22,811
then it shouldn't surprise you

33
00:02:22,811 --> 00:02:24,091
that I know what you're planning.

34
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:26,890
But don't worry.

35
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:28,931
I came here today to talk
about cooperation.

36
00:02:32,091 --> 00:02:33,770
If your commercial building

37
00:02:34,211 --> 00:02:35,770
had a proper snack street inside,

38
00:02:36,770 --> 00:02:38,010
it could actually cover up

39
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:39,211
some irregularities.

40
00:02:39,251 --> 00:02:40,290
Hold on.

41
00:02:40,691 --> 00:02:41,491
Irregularities?

42
00:02:42,050 --> 00:02:43,371
What irregularities?

43
00:02:44,651 --> 00:02:45,971
A commercial building this big

44
00:02:46,811 --> 00:02:48,730
has been empty for more than a year.

45
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,470
Wouldn't that attract attention?

46
00:02:52,170 --> 00:02:53,491
The reason a building this big

47
00:02:53,491 --> 00:02:54,890
hasn't been leased out

48
00:02:55,411 --> 00:02:56,770
is that we're waiting for

49
00:02:56,811 --> 00:02:58,010
the right businesses

50
00:02:58,050 --> 00:02:59,850
and the right people.

51
00:03:00,491 --> 00:03:01,290
Those small vendors

52
00:03:02,131 --> 00:03:02,890
you're proposing

53
00:03:02,890 --> 00:03:04,971
have no brand recognition,

54
00:03:05,050 --> 00:03:06,730
and you want me to cut the rent in half?

55
00:03:07,371 --> 00:03:08,170
Little Genius,

56
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:10,610
or are you actually a Little Dreamer?

57
00:03:16,091 --> 00:03:17,531
If this is about Lysen's

58
00:03:17,531 --> 00:03:18,931
so-called city plan,

59
00:03:18,931 --> 00:03:20,010
I'm not interested.

60
00:03:20,211 --> 00:03:21,131
It's not that.

61
00:03:23,491 --> 00:03:24,450
(Linwei Alley Snack Street)
This is about the financing plan

62
00:03:24,450 --> 00:03:25,610
(Renewal Financing Plan)
of the snack street I'm working on.

63
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:32,371
Jiang Dongchao asked you

64
00:03:32,371 --> 00:03:34,050
to handle the Linwei Alley renewal,

65
00:03:34,371 --> 00:03:35,770
but you're only pushing

66
00:03:35,971 --> 00:03:37,770
the snack street project.

67
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:40,490
Looks like Jiang Dongchao and you
have a disagreement.

68
00:03:42,131 --> 00:03:44,491
Linwei Alley Snack Street
has been around for many years.

69
00:03:44,811 --> 00:03:47,050
A lot of people grew up
eating snacks there.

70
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:48,531
So,

71
00:03:48,651 --> 00:03:49,931
for many people,

72
00:03:49,931 --> 00:03:51,811
it's not just an ordinary alley.

73
00:03:52,010 --> 00:03:53,091
It's a landmark.

74
00:03:53,330 --> 00:03:54,411
It's a kind of sentiment.

75
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:56,211
(Linwei Alley Breakfast Stall)
Landmarks and nostalgia

76
00:03:56,211 --> 00:03:57,330
are huge draws

77
00:03:57,330 --> 00:03:59,010
for consumers.

78
00:03:59,610 --> 00:04:00,570
(Linwei Alley)
So

79
00:04:00,570 --> 00:04:01,971
the name "Linwei Alley" itself

80
00:04:02,371 --> 00:04:03,570
(Lysen Group, creating a better life)
already carries commercial value.

81
00:04:07,287 --> 00:04:08,531
If the transformation

82
00:04:08,531 --> 00:04:10,390
of the Linwei Alley Snack Street
succeeds in your building,

83
00:04:10,411 --> 00:04:11,850
we'll use it as a model

84
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:13,570
to expand and replicate it.

85
00:04:13,691 --> 00:04:14,491
And of course,

86
00:04:14,850 --> 00:04:15,770
Mr. Pengyu,

87
00:04:15,931 --> 00:04:16,970
you'll be

88
00:04:17,010 --> 00:04:18,371
our preferred partner.

89
00:04:26,890 --> 00:04:29,330
To be honest, I don't really care
about making money.

90
00:04:29,812 --> 00:04:32,923
But if this keeps Jiang Dongchao
in check,

91
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:34,851
I'm in.

92
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,450
Come on.

93
00:04:36,811 --> 00:04:37,530
Pass these around.

94
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:39,131
We brought them from Linwei Alley.

95
00:04:39,131 --> 00:04:40,330
Thank you.

96
00:04:40,491 --> 00:04:41,291
Boss,

97
00:04:41,691 --> 00:04:42,851
this is for you.

98
00:04:44,251 --> 00:04:45,051
You eat it.

99
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,900
The best mixed fruit bowl
from the snack street.

100
00:04:47,931 --> 00:04:48,890
Here's your ice cup.

101
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:57,371
Rao Yuci,

102
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:01,650
how much digging have you done on me?

103
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:03,210
Everything.

104
00:05:03,931 --> 00:05:04,890
Including this.

105
00:05:05,251 --> 00:05:06,051
And

106
00:05:07,491 --> 00:05:09,760
your hairstyle, which hasn't changed
in over twenty years.

107
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:12,530
Should I take

108
00:05:12,530 --> 00:05:13,450
all that effort

109
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:14,611
as a way

110
00:05:15,650 --> 00:05:16,731
of buttering me up?

111
00:05:17,570 --> 00:05:18,851
So, I'll help you

112
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:20,851
and approve your plan.

113
00:05:21,131 --> 00:05:22,731
I never asked you to help me.

114
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:25,890
But I did say

115
00:05:26,131 --> 00:05:27,291
if Dept 3 wants to move up,

116
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:28,450
we'll have to stick together.

117
00:05:37,131 --> 00:05:38,450
Tian Tian, start.

118
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:39,970
Over the past few days, Yuci and I

119
00:05:39,970 --> 00:05:41,210
visited several districts

120
00:05:41,291 --> 00:05:42,171
and put together

121
00:05:42,171 --> 00:05:43,931
a more detailed market survey.

122
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:44,931
Please take a look.

123
00:05:44,931 --> 00:05:45,700
(Linwei Alley Snack Street
Renewal Financing Plan)

124
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:47,530
Our city

125
00:05:47,530 --> 00:05:49,611
has a large number
of mobile street vendors.

126
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:50,970
(Project Overview:)
Compared to

127
00:05:50,970 --> 00:05:52,491
(Around 30,000 mobile street vendors)
vendors

128
00:05:52,491 --> 00:05:53,491
with fixed storefronts,

129
00:05:53,491 --> 00:05:55,291
mobile vendors do bring

130
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:57,010
some negative impact

131
00:05:57,010 --> 00:05:58,530
to urban sanitation.

132
00:06:01,825 --> 00:06:02,851
But at the same time,

133
00:06:02,851 --> 00:06:04,090
because they exist,

134
00:06:04,410 --> 00:06:05,770
our city

135
00:06:05,890 --> 00:06:08,291
has more warmth

136
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,640
and a real street-life atmosphere.

137
00:06:10,650 --> 00:06:12,410
Just like Confucius Temple in Nanjing

138
00:06:12,731 --> 00:06:13,970
and the Muslim Quarter in Xi'an,

139
00:06:14,251 --> 00:06:15,530
these places carry generations

140
00:06:15,530 --> 00:06:16,530
of food memories.

141
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:18,570
I came to this city

142
00:06:19,090 --> 00:06:20,851
when I was eighteen.

143
00:06:21,530 --> 00:06:23,090
It was my first year of university.

144
00:06:23,811 --> 00:06:25,491
I'd go there with my coursemates

145
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:26,611
every night

146
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:29,131
for late-night snacks and a stroll.

147
00:06:29,611 --> 00:06:31,010
A lot of my old customers

148
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:33,090
and old friends are here today.

149
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:34,970
I remember

150
00:06:35,811 --> 00:06:37,371
when you were in college,

151
00:06:37,371 --> 00:06:38,611
you used to come here

152
00:06:38,851 --> 00:06:40,051
for malatang

153
00:06:40,171 --> 00:06:41,491
and have secret dates.

154
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:44,611
And now look at you,

155
00:06:44,931 --> 00:06:46,770
you're all married with kids.

156
00:06:47,410 --> 00:06:48,890
Yuci's plan

157
00:06:49,051 --> 00:06:51,210
is to bring these vendors together,

158
00:06:51,570 --> 00:06:53,131
register and manage them uniformly,

159
00:06:53,210 --> 00:06:54,811
from branding and logo design

160
00:06:55,371 --> 00:06:58,410
to site planning, and eventually move them
into a commercial building.

161
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:00,650
(Mixed Fruit Bowl)
That way, we can create

162
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:01,691
a new indoor market model.

163
00:07:01,931 --> 00:07:04,650
We've also finalized the location

164
00:07:05,051 --> 00:07:07,010
for the first phase.

165
00:07:11,562 --> 00:07:14,300
(Linwei Alley)

166
00:07:14,362 --> 00:07:15,812
(Xianxian Malatang,
A'ertou Food Store)

167
00:07:15,851 --> 00:07:16,811
This city is huge.

168
00:07:17,371 --> 00:07:19,131
(Demolition)
All of us are trying to find

169
00:07:19,131 --> 00:07:20,731
a place that belongs to us.

170
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:23,291
But along the way,

171
00:07:23,491 --> 00:07:24,530
(Demolition)
it's easy to forget to ask ourselves

172
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:26,690
what all this hustle and bustle

173
00:07:26,890 --> 00:07:28,131
is really for.

174
00:07:29,731 --> 00:07:30,530
In the end,

175
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,491
it comes down to this.

176
00:07:34,410 --> 00:07:35,731
"Warmth on a cold night,

177
00:07:36,530 --> 00:07:38,090
and the comforting aroma of a hot food."

178
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:41,731
Well said!

179
00:07:42,371 --> 00:07:43,371
Great job, Tian Tian.

180
00:07:57,090 --> 00:07:58,890
Mr. Yu, you understand this better
than I do.

181
00:08:00,371 --> 00:08:02,010
Money itself is never a bad thing.

182
00:08:03,611 --> 00:08:04,410
But when money

183
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,770
goes to the people who need it,

184
00:08:06,970 --> 00:08:08,010
that's even better.

185
00:08:08,570 --> 00:08:09,371
Right?

186
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:14,611
How much funding are you asking for?

187
00:08:28,530 --> 00:08:30,171
Ideals always sound beautiful,

188
00:08:32,331 --> 00:08:34,371
but reality often turns out otherwise.

189
00:08:36,930 --> 00:08:37,731
Boss.

190
00:08:38,650 --> 00:08:39,331
(Project Overview)
Boss.

191
00:08:39,331 --> 00:08:40,131
Mr. Yu.

192
00:08:41,251 --> 00:08:42,050
Mr. Yu.

193
00:08:47,731 --> 00:08:49,690
It's fine. Let him go.

194
00:09:00,451 --> 00:09:02,331
(Even if no one helps me,)

195
00:09:03,170 --> 00:09:04,690
(I'll still carry out my plan)

196
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:06,491
(step by step.)

197
00:09:13,987 --> 00:09:16,028
This is a joke, don't you think so?

198
00:09:16,211 --> 00:09:18,690
A company worth tens of billions
helping a few street vendors?

199
00:09:18,810 --> 00:09:19,770
People would think

200
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:20,971
we're crazy.

201
00:09:20,971 --> 00:09:22,451
This is absurd.

202
00:09:23,131 --> 00:09:24,131
Maybe geniuses

203
00:09:24,131 --> 00:09:25,371
think differently from us.

204
00:09:25,371 --> 00:09:26,050
Genius?

205
00:09:26,050 --> 00:09:27,371
Looks more like an idiot to me.

206
00:09:34,170 --> 00:09:34,971
Mr. Yu,

207
00:09:35,851 --> 00:09:38,331
I feel like she's a lot like you.

208
00:09:40,451 --> 00:09:41,971
Are you saying I'm an idiot?

209
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,650
I wouldn't call you an idiot.

210
00:09:45,971 --> 00:09:47,530
At most, it's idealism.

211
00:09:48,611 --> 00:09:49,451
I still remember

212
00:09:49,810 --> 00:09:50,690
when you went

213
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:53,611
to see Mr. Jiang to raise funds for
that rare disease project,

214
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:54,571
you said,

215
00:09:56,371 --> 00:09:57,290
"If this project

216
00:09:57,290 --> 00:09:58,611
has no commercial value,

217
00:09:58,851 --> 00:10:00,810
I'll run around the whole company naked."

218
00:10:04,370 --> 00:10:05,290
Thinking about it now,

219
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:06,851
I must've been sick in the head.

220
00:10:09,611 --> 00:10:10,410
Actually,

221
00:10:10,971 --> 00:10:11,971
we all know

222
00:10:12,571 --> 00:10:14,170
you didn't give up,

223
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,211
even though Mr. Jiang rejected you.

224
00:10:17,131 --> 00:10:17,930
All these years,

225
00:10:18,110 --> 00:10:20,760
you've still been out there
trying to raise funds for that project.

226
00:10:26,775 --> 00:10:29,450
(Seven years earlier)

227
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:32,331
Where's Ren Jing?

228
00:10:32,971 --> 00:10:34,611
Still thinking about my Ren Jing?

229
00:10:35,451 --> 00:10:36,251
She's in a meeting.

230
00:10:36,451 --> 00:10:37,770
She'll come after work.

231
00:10:39,410 --> 00:10:40,971
What's the point?

232
00:10:41,971 --> 00:10:43,410
My illness

233
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:45,930
has no cure.

234
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:48,211
Looks like

235
00:10:49,410 --> 00:10:51,571
the medicine won't come in time.

236
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:54,451
You... Sometimes,

237
00:10:54,451 --> 00:10:55,770
you're just too pessimistic.

238
00:10:58,170 --> 00:10:59,170
Peidong,

239
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:03,650
can you promise me one thing?

240
00:11:07,930 --> 00:11:12,290
Please take care of my wife and kid.

241
00:11:15,290 --> 00:11:16,131
Don't worry.

242
00:11:18,451 --> 00:11:20,971
When she finds a new boyfriend one day,

243
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:22,770
I'll vet him for you.

244
00:11:23,331 --> 00:11:24,091
First thing I'll do

245
00:11:24,091 --> 00:11:26,371
is take him to the hospital
for a check-up.

246
00:11:26,371 --> 00:11:28,110
She can't keep ending up
with sickly guys.

247
00:11:36,211 --> 00:11:39,971
If you ever make it big,

248
00:11:40,971 --> 00:11:45,170
besides helping me,

249
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:48,371
please help the other patients too.

250
00:11:53,611 --> 00:11:54,571
In the end, this disease

251
00:11:54,571 --> 00:11:55,451
is nothing

252
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:57,930
but money.

253
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:01,611
I've plenty of ways to deal with money.

254
00:12:09,451 --> 00:12:10,690
Don't end up like me,

255
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:12,211
buried deep in debt.

256
00:12:15,690 --> 00:12:16,491
Director Liu,

257
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:17,930
(Rare Disease Center)
I haven't come here much

258
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:19,971
after my friend passed away.

259
00:12:20,170 --> 00:12:21,810
Right. Recently, I've been in contact

260
00:12:21,810 --> 00:12:24,451
(Compassion of a Healer)
with a few foundations in this field.

261
00:12:24,491 --> 00:12:26,010
But nothing has worked out so far.

262
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:28,530
So you're short on funds again...

263
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:31,110
The number of patients has increased?

264
00:12:31,290 --> 00:12:32,251
A few days ago,

265
00:12:32,491 --> 00:12:33,571
a volunteer

266
00:12:33,571 --> 00:12:35,170
contacted us.

267
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:37,211
She brought some donated funds
and supplies.

268
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:39,170
But

269
00:12:39,170 --> 00:12:40,290
she had one condition.

270
00:12:40,650 --> 00:12:42,371
When the donation was made,

271
00:12:42,571 --> 00:12:44,650
you had to be present.

272
00:12:46,010 --> 00:12:47,170
I had to be there?

273
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:51,690
Please come in.

274
00:12:57,770 --> 00:12:58,571
Mr. Yu,

275
00:12:59,211 --> 00:13:00,010
long time no see.

276
00:13:03,731 --> 00:13:04,851
Careful with that.

277
00:13:07,851 --> 00:13:08,650
Chen.

278
00:13:10,211 --> 00:13:11,010
Boss Yu.

279
00:13:12,211 --> 00:13:13,010
Excuse me?

280
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:14,690
Peidong.

281
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,010
Thanks.

282
00:13:16,571 --> 00:13:17,810
All the supplies are here.

283
00:13:17,810 --> 00:13:18,810
You can double-check them later.

284
00:13:18,810 --> 00:13:19,930
If there's any issue,

285
00:13:19,971 --> 00:13:20,890
contact me.

286
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:23,990
It's so hot today.
Thank you for your hard work.

287
00:13:24,010 --> 00:13:25,371
I should be thanking you instead.

288
00:13:25,770 --> 00:13:27,770
Because of the money and supplies
you donated,

289
00:13:27,790 --> 00:13:29,211
my son can finally
receive treatment here

290
00:13:29,211 --> 00:13:30,371
without worry.

291
00:13:31,451 --> 00:13:32,930
One from the parents' group chat

292
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:34,810
says they want to thank you properly.

293
00:13:35,371 --> 00:13:36,731
No need for that.

294
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:38,571
I should get going.

295
00:13:38,571 --> 00:13:39,211
Go on.

296
00:13:44,930 --> 00:13:45,731
Boss Yu,

297
00:13:47,371 --> 00:13:49,491
the money you donated saves lives.

298
00:13:59,050 --> 00:14:00,370
What is this, a wake or something?

299
00:14:03,290 --> 00:14:04,251
Drive safe.

300
00:14:09,611 --> 00:14:11,650
It feels great when your mind
isn't distracted.

301
00:14:17,611 --> 00:14:20,131
After I left, there must've been
rumors everywhere.

302
00:14:22,571 --> 00:14:23,810
Some said you went crazy.

303
00:14:24,611 --> 00:14:25,770
Some said you ran away.

304
00:14:25,851 --> 00:14:26,770
Some even said...

305
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:31,010
What are those?

306
00:14:33,091 --> 00:14:34,770
Rao Yuci donated them.

307
00:14:35,331 --> 00:14:36,131
Who?

308
00:14:36,971 --> 00:14:37,770
Rao Yuci.

309
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:40,211
I'm just

310
00:14:40,410 --> 00:14:41,611
acting as a liaison.

311
00:14:46,690 --> 00:14:47,491
Before,

312
00:14:49,170 --> 00:14:50,211
my cowardice and greed

313
00:14:50,211 --> 00:14:52,211
made me do a lot of wrong things.

314
00:14:54,170 --> 00:14:55,371
I couldn't even face

315
00:14:55,371 --> 00:14:56,290
who I really was.

316
00:14:59,131 --> 00:15:00,731
It was Rao Yuci who woke me up.

317
00:15:01,571 --> 00:15:02,650
After leaving the company,

318
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:05,290
I focused on working,
paying off my debts,

319
00:15:05,530 --> 00:15:06,930
and taking care of my sick father.

320
00:15:07,731 --> 00:15:08,530
That kind of life

321
00:15:08,530 --> 00:15:09,890
made me feel grounded.

322
00:15:11,890 --> 00:15:13,331
I came here to repay a debt.

323
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:16,010
I owe Rao Yuci too much.

324
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:30,690
Many patients here

325
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:33,770
are younger than me.

326
00:15:35,571 --> 00:15:38,091
They need help.

327
00:15:40,211 --> 00:15:41,650
Those outsiders

328
00:15:42,930 --> 00:15:44,491
may think this industry

329
00:15:45,131 --> 00:15:46,650
is only about making money,

330
00:15:47,371 --> 00:15:50,410
but investing in an ideal

331
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:54,731
and helping people who need help,

332
00:15:55,611 --> 00:15:58,731
someone has to do it.

333
00:15:58,731 --> 00:15:59,571
A few years ago,

334
00:16:00,091 --> 00:16:01,650
you raised charity funds

335
00:16:02,010 --> 00:16:03,010
for these patients.

336
00:16:03,251 --> 00:16:05,010
You were full of passion back then.

337
00:16:05,810 --> 00:16:08,331
Nothing could stop you.

338
00:16:09,211 --> 00:16:10,650
You were happy, weren't you?

339
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:19,587
(Linwei Alley Snack Food
Renewal Financing Plan)

340
00:16:19,637 --> 00:16:23,425
(Yu Peidong: After careful consideration,
the snack street project can proceed.)

341
00:16:23,425 --> 00:16:25,012
(Sima Yang: !!! Boss is the best!!!)

342
00:16:25,012 --> 00:16:26,150
(Tian Tian: That's great!
Thank you, Mr. Yu.)

343
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:27,537
(Tian Tian: @RaoYuci Yuci!)

344
00:16:27,690 --> 00:16:28,491
(Wang Meng: We'll follow your lead.)
Come on.

345
00:16:28,491 --> 00:16:29,451
(Wang Meng: We'll follow your lead.)
Something just struck me.

346
00:16:30,170 --> 00:16:32,010
(Rao Yuci: Thank you.)
Water, electricity, and fire safety.

347
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:33,731
Make sure you coordinate with them.

348
00:16:33,731 --> 00:16:35,050
Especially the old electrical wiring.

349
00:16:35,050 --> 00:16:36,851
That needs extra attention.

350
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:38,611
Don't take it lightly.

351
00:16:38,611 --> 00:16:39,251
Hello?

352
00:16:40,491 --> 00:16:41,091
Also,

353
00:16:41,091 --> 00:16:41,731
another thing.

354
00:16:41,731 --> 00:16:42,930
Make sure to emphasize

355
00:16:42,930 --> 00:16:44,251
food safety with them.

356
00:16:44,251 --> 00:16:46,091
From sourcing raw ingredients
to processing to storage,

357
00:16:46,091 --> 00:16:46,770
every step

358
00:16:46,770 --> 00:16:48,050
must strictly follow regulations.

359
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:49,491
If we want to build this
into a strong brand,

360
00:16:49,491 --> 00:16:50,290
we can't cut corners.

361
00:16:50,290 --> 00:16:50,851
Follow the rules.

362
00:16:50,851 --> 00:16:51,451
Don't worry, Miss Meng.

363
00:16:51,451 --> 00:16:52,091
Yes.

364
00:16:52,251 --> 00:16:53,251
We got this.

365
00:16:55,131 --> 00:16:56,890
Rao Yuci does have some charm.

366
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,899
Even Yu Peidong was convinced by her.

367
00:17:01,010 --> 00:17:02,491
It's not just Yu Peidong though.

368
00:17:02,530 --> 00:17:03,290
Mr. Jiang,

369
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:04,771
you didn't stop her either, did you?

370
00:17:04,970 --> 00:17:06,410
Why would I stop her?

371
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:07,890
This project

372
00:17:07,890 --> 00:17:08,930
doesn't cost much money.

373
00:17:09,410 --> 00:17:10,650
I just want to see

374
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:12,611
what she's trying to do.

375
00:17:14,325 --> 00:17:15,637
Aren't you curious?

376
00:17:20,490 --> 00:17:21,410
Oh, right, Mr. Jiang.

377
00:17:21,730 --> 00:17:22,331
Regarding

378
00:17:22,331 --> 00:17:23,490
the Linwei Alley City Plan,

379
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:24,960
I went to the construction site
a couple of days ago.

380
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:26,011
I ran into

381
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,371
our old friend.

382
00:17:28,331 --> 00:17:29,131
Who?

383
00:17:32,011 --> 00:17:32,811
Zhou Lufeng.

384
00:17:50,650 --> 00:17:51,450
Mr. Jiang.

385
00:17:51,450 --> 00:18:01,900
(Baiying Business Investigation)

386
00:18:05,530 --> 00:18:07,020
The prices are posted on the entrance.

387
00:18:07,091 --> 00:18:08,930
Reports and investigation fees
are all listed.

388
00:18:08,930 --> 00:18:10,131
We'll talk after you read it.

389
00:18:17,851 --> 00:18:18,650
Mr. Zhou.

390
00:18:20,611 --> 00:18:21,490
Long time no see.

391
00:18:24,630 --> 00:18:26,210
Mr. Jiang, please don't mind the place.

392
00:18:26,210 --> 00:18:28,970
It's a small office.

393
00:18:29,611 --> 00:18:30,410
Here.

394
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,131
Not at all.

395
00:18:32,690 --> 00:18:34,490
Back then, if anyone wanted to have tea

396
00:18:34,490 --> 00:18:35,250
with you,

397
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:37,690
they had to line up for it.

398
00:18:39,011 --> 00:18:41,571
It's been many years since we last met.

399
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:43,170
Yes.

400
00:18:43,291 --> 00:18:45,170
I suppose

401
00:18:45,170 --> 00:18:46,970
it was after Lysen's second
Boundary Forum

402
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,011
that you

403
00:18:50,490 --> 00:18:51,930
disappeared.

404
00:18:53,730 --> 00:18:54,531
Yes.

405
00:18:55,531 --> 00:18:57,611
After that public speech

406
00:18:57,611 --> 00:18:58,331
when I criticized

407
00:18:58,331 --> 00:18:59,970
Lysen's reckless expansion,

408
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:01,890
I was forced to disappear.

409
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:05,091
Right.

410
00:19:06,170 --> 00:19:07,210
Lysen's strategy back then

411
00:19:07,210 --> 00:19:08,670
was to move forward step by step
in a careful manner.

412
00:19:09,091 --> 00:19:09,890
That explains

413
00:19:11,170 --> 00:19:12,490
why people misunderstood.

414
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:13,990
Mr. Jiang, you've got the wrong idea.

415
00:19:14,210 --> 00:19:15,131
I barely remember

416
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:17,170
those things anymore.

417
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:19,250
I'm doing fine now.

418
00:19:19,690 --> 00:19:21,011
What happens in the big market now

419
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,650
has nothing to do with me anymore.

420
00:19:26,811 --> 00:19:28,410
Big or small,

421
00:19:28,410 --> 00:19:29,730
those are labels outsiders use.

422
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:32,790
People in the industry know
that small things decide big outcomes.

423
00:19:33,490 --> 00:19:35,890
Mr. Zhou, you say you don't care about
big matters anymore,

424
00:19:37,131 --> 00:19:38,011
but it seems

425
00:19:38,011 --> 00:19:39,291
otherwise.

426
00:19:41,371 --> 00:19:42,170
I heard

427
00:19:42,851 --> 00:19:44,410
you visited our construction site

428
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:46,011
for the Linwei Alley City Plan.

429
00:19:46,531 --> 00:19:47,730
If Bosi

430
00:19:47,730 --> 00:19:48,371
hired you

431
00:19:48,371 --> 00:19:49,410
to investigate us,

432
00:19:50,650 --> 00:19:52,131
you could've come straight to me.

433
00:19:56,450 --> 00:19:57,371
Someone did ask me

434
00:19:58,331 --> 00:19:59,771
to investigate this project.

435
00:20:01,091 --> 00:20:02,371
It wasn't Bosi.

436
00:20:15,091 --> 00:20:16,210
They knew you were coming

437
00:20:17,531 --> 00:20:19,450
and asked me to hand this over to you.

438
00:20:19,450 --> 00:20:20,180
(Investigation Report on
Green Building Materials Firms)

439
00:20:21,611 --> 00:20:23,051
Take some time to read it.

440
00:20:23,331 --> 00:20:25,650
There's something very interesting
in there.

441
00:20:30,210 --> 00:20:31,771
This client you mentioned

442
00:20:33,371 --> 00:20:34,450
is Rao Yuci?

443
00:20:42,611 --> 00:20:43,410
Rao Yuci.

444
00:20:48,811 --> 00:20:49,611
Morning.

445
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:50,450
Morning.

446
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:52,090
You look pretty happy.

447
00:20:52,730 --> 00:20:53,611
To be honest,

448
00:20:54,531 --> 00:20:56,851
I haven't felt this happy
in this building for a long time.

449
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:58,091
Thank you.

450
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:00,051
You helped me get back

451
00:21:00,051 --> 00:21:02,091
the drive I had when I first joined Lysen.

452
00:21:03,771 --> 00:21:05,210
I have a gift for you.

453
00:21:12,571 --> 00:21:13,531
Go to work already.

454
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:18,990
Once you walk through this door,
you can't smile.

455
00:21:19,051 --> 00:21:20,291
Put that smile away.

456
00:21:20,450 --> 00:21:21,250
Look around.

457
00:21:21,490 --> 00:21:22,930
Everyone in this building is sick.

458
00:21:23,011 --> 00:21:24,450
Can't smile or make friends.

459
00:21:28,131 --> 00:21:29,730
There's something I don't understand.

460
00:21:30,331 --> 00:21:32,571
You could've taken over
the Linwei Alley City Plan.

461
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,640
It doesn't conflict
with the snack street project.

462
00:21:34,650 --> 00:21:35,851
Aren't you basically

463
00:21:35,851 --> 00:21:38,331
handing the opportunity
Mr. Jiang gave you right back to him?

464
00:21:38,771 --> 00:21:40,051
Who said I handed it back?

465
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:41,580
The opportunity is still in my hands.

466
00:21:56,011 --> 00:21:56,490
Alright.

467
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:57,170
Mr. Rao.

468
00:21:58,011 --> 00:21:58,811
Liangliang.

469
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:05,930
The money I'm putting in here
isn't just mine and my wife's,

470
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,760
it's also money borrowed
from relatives and friends.

471
00:22:07,771 --> 00:22:09,531
Some of it is a bank loan.

472
00:22:10,450 --> 00:22:11,291
Are you sure

473
00:22:11,690 --> 00:22:13,210
this plan won't go wrong?

474
00:22:14,331 --> 00:22:16,170
Ever since Mr. Jiang joined Lysen,

475
00:22:16,291 --> 00:22:17,091
acquiring Bosi

476
00:22:17,091 --> 00:22:18,611
has been his dream.

477
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:20,611
Now that the opportunity
is finally right in front of him,

478
00:22:20,611 --> 00:22:22,210
there's no way he'll give it up.

479
00:22:22,930 --> 00:22:24,650
If you're worried,

480
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:26,490
you can take your money back.

481
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:28,291
No, that's not what I mean.

482
00:22:28,810 --> 00:22:31,291
It took me a lot of effort
to convince those then households

483
00:22:31,291 --> 00:22:32,450
in Linwei Alley.

484
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:35,170
After we buy those ten properties,

485
00:22:35,331 --> 00:22:37,131
Lysen has to take over them.

486
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,970
The contract of this project is signed
under my company's name.

487
00:22:39,970 --> 00:22:41,011
I can cover

488
00:22:41,011 --> 00:22:42,131
the initial funding.

489
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:43,051
But if Lysen

490
00:22:43,051 --> 00:22:44,690
refuses to take over later,

491
00:22:45,331 --> 00:22:46,851
my cash flow

492
00:22:47,287 --> 00:22:48,326
will collapse.

493
00:22:49,851 --> 00:22:51,011
Don't worry, Mr. Rao.

494
00:22:51,051 --> 00:22:52,170
Nothing will go wrong.

495
00:22:53,291 --> 00:22:55,291
Mr. Rao, the contract has been checked.

496
00:22:55,291 --> 00:22:56,120
Everything looks good.

497
00:22:56,131 --> 00:22:57,371
You can sign it now.

498
00:22:57,371 --> 00:22:58,170
Alright.

499
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:01,650
I'll take the gamble.

500
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:03,051
I trust you.

501
00:23:03,051 --> 00:23:04,331
You won't bring me bad luck

502
00:23:04,571 --> 00:23:06,331
as my daughter does.

503
00:23:07,730 --> 00:23:08,851
Sign on the last page

504
00:23:08,851 --> 00:23:09,650
of the contract.

505
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:11,051
Alright.

506
00:23:12,410 --> 00:23:13,210
Over here.

507
00:23:15,487 --> 00:23:17,825
(Rao Shusheng)

508
00:23:18,291 --> 00:23:19,091
Okay.

509
00:23:26,291 --> 00:23:27,650
(Five years earlier)
I told you before.

510
00:23:27,650 --> 00:23:28,930
I investigated that company.

511
00:23:28,930 --> 00:23:30,250
It's a scam.

512
00:23:30,531 --> 00:23:32,131
Rao Shusheng, you're too greedy.

513
00:23:32,410 --> 00:23:33,250
What did I do wrong?

514
00:23:33,571 --> 00:23:34,450
I did nothing wrong.

515
00:23:35,291 --> 00:23:37,051
I was just unlucky.

516
00:23:37,131 --> 00:23:37,970
All of this happened

517
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:38,930
because of you, jinx.

518
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:39,730
Rao Yuci.

519
00:23:49,571 --> 00:23:50,930
What happened?

520
00:23:52,170 --> 00:23:53,690
He invested in futures

521
00:23:54,370 --> 00:23:55,371
and lost a lot of money.

522
00:23:56,210 --> 00:23:57,650
He even took my mom's savings.

523
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:00,331
How much did he lose? A lot?

524
00:24:01,811 --> 00:24:02,690
The problem is,

525
00:24:02,690 --> 00:24:05,110
every decision he makes
always ends up dragging my mom down.

526
00:24:05,970 --> 00:24:06,970
When I was little,

527
00:24:07,650 --> 00:24:09,531
his factory caught fire.

528
00:24:09,771 --> 00:24:10,571
Two workers

529
00:24:11,531 --> 00:24:12,771
died in the accident.

530
00:24:12,887 --> 00:24:14,690
The compensation

531
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:17,131
was all paid with money
my mom earned through hard work.

532
00:24:17,291 --> 00:24:18,091
And him?

533
00:24:18,250 --> 00:24:19,811
He never even apologized.

534
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:22,490
Yuci,

535
00:24:22,730 --> 00:24:24,091
he's your father.

536
00:24:24,531 --> 00:24:26,091
If you expose him like that,

537
00:24:26,091 --> 00:24:27,571
he won't be able to take it.

538
00:24:28,571 --> 00:24:30,131
Sometimes when you're too serious,

539
00:24:30,450 --> 00:24:31,930
it puts pressure on him

540
00:24:32,131 --> 00:24:33,331
and makes him fear.

541
00:24:33,650 --> 00:24:34,490
Do you understand?

542
00:24:39,410 --> 00:24:40,210
Liangliang,

543
00:24:41,371 --> 00:24:42,091
I wish Yuci

544
00:24:42,091 --> 00:24:43,410
could be more like you.

545
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:45,051
I really envy your dad

546
00:24:45,670 --> 00:24:47,091
for having an understanding daughter

547
00:24:47,212 --> 00:24:48,652
like you.

548
00:24:52,325 --> 00:24:53,875
Mr. Rao, I understand you.

549
00:24:54,490 --> 00:24:56,331
All you want is for Yuci

550
00:24:56,762 --> 00:24:58,522
to support you unconditionally.

551
00:24:58,612 --> 00:25:00,132
After all, she's your daughter.

552
00:25:00,875 --> 00:25:02,235
I'm doing all this for this family.

553
00:25:03,730 --> 00:25:04,650
I don't get

554
00:25:04,650 --> 00:25:05,650
why she always

555
00:25:05,650 --> 00:25:07,410
doubts me.

556
00:25:08,811 --> 00:25:10,771
No father and daughter are born enemies.

557
00:25:11,091 --> 00:25:12,450
But she and I...

558
00:25:18,771 --> 00:25:19,830
Ever since she was little,

559
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:21,531
everyone said

560
00:25:21,531 --> 00:25:23,291
she was smart and sweet.

561
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:25,531
But I can only see

562
00:25:25,531 --> 00:25:27,250
that judgmental look
when she looks at me.

563
00:25:33,011 --> 00:25:33,930
(Rao Yuci,)

564
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:36,410
(you're not gaining a foothold)

565
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,611
(with Jiang Dongchao.)

566
00:25:38,730 --> 00:25:39,811
Do you need any help?

567
00:25:40,091 --> 00:25:40,890
No.

568
00:25:41,291 --> 00:25:42,490
I can manage.

569
00:25:43,611 --> 00:25:45,131
(These ten property deeds)

570
00:25:45,571 --> 00:25:47,091
(are my proof of loyalty.)

571
00:25:47,510 --> 00:25:48,811
(I'm going to completely destroy)

572
00:25:48,811 --> 00:25:49,970
(Jiang Dongchao's trust)

573
00:25:50,091 --> 00:25:51,450
(in you.)

574
00:25:52,450 --> 00:25:56,675
(Demolition)

575
00:25:57,051 --> 00:25:57,811
Didn't we agree

576
00:25:57,811 --> 00:25:59,210
to move out in three days?

577
00:25:59,210 --> 00:26:00,011
We haven't finished

578
00:26:00,011 --> 00:26:01,210
packing yet.

579
00:26:01,210 --> 00:26:01,730
Look,

580
00:26:01,730 --> 00:26:03,011
we've known each other for years.

581
00:26:03,011 --> 00:26:04,450
Can't you cut us some slack?

582
00:26:04,450 --> 00:26:07,490
Yes, give us a little more time.

583
00:26:07,510 --> 00:26:08,650
We don't have a choice either.

584
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:09,091
Right.

585
00:26:09,091 --> 00:26:10,730
Please try to understand us, okay?

586
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:11,930
The building doesn't belong
to us anymore.

587
00:26:11,930 --> 00:26:12,811
It's not ours now.

588
00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:14,490
The ownership has been transferred.

589
00:26:14,490 --> 00:26:16,450
The new landlord
wants the place vacated immediately.

590
00:26:16,450 --> 00:26:17,730
There's nothing I can do.

591
00:26:17,730 --> 00:26:18,131
Exactly.

592
00:26:18,131 --> 00:26:19,811
But if you make us move out now,

593
00:26:19,811 --> 00:26:20,970
where is my whole family

594
00:26:21,131 --> 00:26:22,291
supposed to live?

595
00:26:22,410 --> 00:26:23,690
Live wherever I want.

596
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:24,851
Why are you asking us?

597
00:26:24,851 --> 00:26:26,091
How would we know?

598
00:26:36,730 --> 00:26:37,851
Don't fight. Stop it.

599
00:26:37,851 --> 00:26:38,690
What's going on here?

600
00:26:38,690 --> 00:26:39,851
Thank goodness you're here, Mr. Chen.

601
00:26:39,851 --> 00:26:40,531
What are we supposed to do?

602
00:26:40,531 --> 00:26:42,291
The landlord suddenly told us
to move out.

603
00:26:42,450 --> 00:26:44,011
Why such short notice?

604
00:26:45,650 --> 00:26:46,450
Hello, Tian Tian?

605
00:26:47,410 --> 00:26:48,210
Ms. Chen.

606
00:26:54,051 --> 00:26:55,011
Submit this through OA.

607
00:26:55,611 --> 00:26:58,450
But Ms. Chen, there are ten house owners
in Linwei Alley

608
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:00,080
who suddenly demanded
that the tenants move today.

609
00:27:00,091 --> 00:27:01,450
The system takes time,

610
00:27:01,811 --> 00:27:03,771
so I brought the document
directly to you.

611
00:27:03,771 --> 00:27:05,720
This is something
the Dept 3 is working on.

612
00:27:05,730 --> 00:27:06,970
We don't have the budget for it.

613
00:27:07,410 --> 00:27:08,091
And besides,

614
00:27:08,091 --> 00:27:09,571
we're not a charity.

615
00:27:09,580 --> 00:27:11,490
It was Dept 3's idea
to help these street vendors

616
00:27:11,490 --> 00:27:12,930
in the first place.

617
00:27:12,930 --> 00:27:15,811
But Ms. Chen, you're also in charge
of the Linwei Alley project.

618
00:27:15,811 --> 00:27:17,331
If you disagree,

619
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:19,291
you can talk to Mr. Jiang.

620
00:27:22,011 --> 00:27:22,690
Ms. Chen...

621
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:23,450
Right now.

622
00:27:24,250 --> 00:27:25,371
At once.

623
00:27:25,970 --> 00:27:27,091
Please leave my office.

624
00:27:38,011 --> 00:27:39,710
Notify every moving
and logistics company

625
00:27:39,771 --> 00:27:41,490
in the name of Lysen Group.

626
00:27:42,011 --> 00:27:43,371
If any company helps with the move

627
00:27:43,371 --> 00:27:44,531
in the Linwei Alley today,

628
00:27:45,011 --> 00:27:47,131
Lysen will never work with them again.

629
00:27:48,571 --> 00:27:50,371
We've contacted all the moving companies.

630
00:27:50,371 --> 00:27:51,331
Even when we offered more money,
none of them would come.

631
00:27:51,371 --> 00:27:52,170
Why?

632
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:53,670
They didn't give a reason.

633
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,210
Uh,

634
00:27:55,531 --> 00:27:57,011
we tried contacting a few ourselves.

635
00:27:57,011 --> 00:27:58,390
They all said
they had no trucks available.

636
00:27:58,531 --> 00:27:59,611
What do we do now?

637
00:27:59,930 --> 00:28:01,291
We're asked to move out today.

638
00:28:02,051 --> 00:28:03,011
We've tried everything.

639
00:28:03,011 --> 00:28:04,131
We can't get a truck.

640
00:28:04,170 --> 00:28:05,250
Alright.

641
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:06,611
Let's make use of the time

642
00:28:06,611 --> 00:28:07,730
we still have.

643
00:28:07,730 --> 00:28:08,490
You all

644
00:28:08,490 --> 00:28:09,611
go pack everything up.

645
00:28:09,611 --> 00:28:10,131
Go ahead.

646
00:28:10,131 --> 00:28:10,890
Let's start moving.

647
00:28:10,890 --> 00:28:12,131
We'll figure out the trucks.

648
00:28:12,131 --> 00:28:12,851
Alright?

649
00:28:12,851 --> 00:28:13,410
Alright.

650
00:28:13,410 --> 00:28:15,051
Thank you.

651
00:28:15,450 --> 00:28:16,331
Thank you.

652
00:28:16,490 --> 00:28:17,650
Thank you.

653
00:28:17,650 --> 00:28:18,571
Don't worry.

654
00:28:18,571 --> 00:28:19,531
We'll solve it.

655
00:28:24,737 --> 00:28:25,825
(Group chat (3)
Rao Yuci: This is a temporary group.)

656
00:28:25,825 --> 00:28:28,075
(The vendors at Linwei Alley can't find
any trucks. @Chen, we need your help.)

657
00:28:28,075 --> 00:28:30,062
(Chen: No problem. I'll do everything
I can. How many trucks do you need?)

658
00:28:30,112 --> 00:28:32,800
(Rao Yuci: Thank you, Chen.
@Mr. Yu, please coordinate with Chen.)

659
00:28:32,862 --> 00:28:35,375
(Yu Peidong: Roger that.
You call the shot now!)

660
00:28:36,811 --> 00:28:38,890
I didn't get anything done this morning.

661
00:28:38,890 --> 00:28:40,011
Just making phone calls.

662
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:41,131
What's wrong, Liang?

663
00:28:42,531 --> 00:28:44,371
It's about the Linwei Alley.

664
00:28:45,811 --> 00:28:48,410
Didn't the announcement say
they would move out in three days?

665
00:28:49,051 --> 00:28:49,970
No idea

666
00:28:49,970 --> 00:28:51,051
why it has to be today.

667
00:28:51,210 --> 00:28:52,771
Ms. Chen is furious.

668
00:28:52,771 --> 00:28:53,730
She told everyone

669
00:28:53,771 --> 00:28:55,051
that if any logistics company

670
00:28:55,051 --> 00:28:55,811
steps in,

671
00:28:55,811 --> 00:28:57,650
Lysen will never work with them again.

672
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:05,690
Chen.

673
00:29:08,410 --> 00:29:09,210
Alright.

674
00:29:10,771 --> 00:29:11,571
Done eating?

675
00:29:13,590 --> 00:29:14,571
If you're done, let's go.

676
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:16,331
- Where?
- Where?

677
00:29:17,131 --> 00:29:17,930
Linwei Alley.

678
00:29:20,051 --> 00:29:20,851
Yes.

679
00:29:21,490 --> 00:29:22,650
We're going to Linwei Alley.

680
00:29:31,051 --> 00:29:32,531
Do you mind sitting in one of them?

681
00:29:32,531 --> 00:29:33,250
Of course.

682
00:29:33,410 --> 00:29:34,690
That's awesome, Boss.

683
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:35,410
Let's go.

684
00:29:35,851 --> 00:29:36,690
Time to get to work.

685
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,091
I'll take the truck at the back.

686
00:29:38,091 --> 00:29:38,331
Okay.

687
00:29:38,331 --> 00:29:39,371
I'll take this one.

688
00:29:39,371 --> 00:29:43,612
♪What's playing on the TV
another annoying heartbreak song♪

689
00:29:43,612 --> 00:29:45,087
♪Maybe I just woke up too early♪

690
00:29:45,087 --> 00:29:48,562
♪This pointless rain
washes all my color away♪

691
00:29:48,562 --> 00:29:50,187
♪Your message shows as read♪

692
00:29:50,210 --> 00:29:50,970
Give it a moment.

693
00:29:50,970 --> 00:29:51,970
Don't worry.

694
00:29:52,725 --> 00:29:55,300
♪Maybe my passion burned too hot♪

695
00:29:55,300 --> 00:29:57,925
♪Boiling over till it lost its flame♪

696
00:29:57,925 --> 00:29:59,487
♪We always pass each other by♪

697
00:29:59,487 --> 00:30:01,424
♪Then dive back into the crowd again♪

698
00:30:01,475 --> 00:30:03,875
♪Who would listen to
my sleepless nights♪

699
00:30:03,875 --> 00:30:06,212
♪Who cares about
the stars or the weather♪

700
00:30:06,250 --> 00:30:08,437
♪None of it has anything to do with me♪

701
00:30:08,437 --> 00:30:10,212
♪The little shop down the street♪

702
00:30:11,011 --> 00:30:12,250
The trucks are here!

703
00:30:12,250 --> 00:30:12,970
They're here.

704
00:30:13,450 --> 00:30:14,531
They're here!

705
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:18,562
♪Good night, world♪

706
00:30:18,662 --> 00:30:20,175
♪The moon has risen♪

707
00:30:20,175 --> 00:30:22,100
♪How could the lonely fall asleep♪

708
00:30:22,170 --> 00:30:22,970
So many trucks?

709
00:30:23,012 --> 00:30:25,050
♪The silence of the world
feels just right♪

710
00:30:25,131 --> 00:30:27,131
There are plenty of them.

711
00:30:27,875 --> 00:30:29,625
♪Good night, world♪

712
00:30:29,625 --> 00:30:32,187
♪It's time for my own lonely celebration♪

713
00:30:33,771 --> 00:30:34,571
Here we are.

714
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:36,811
Yuci, we're here to help.

715
00:30:36,811 --> 00:30:37,690
We're here to help.

716
00:30:38,771 --> 00:30:40,051
We have so many helpers.

717
00:30:40,091 --> 00:30:40,890
Thanks, everyone.

718
00:30:41,611 --> 00:30:42,410
Let's get to work.

719
00:30:43,250 --> 00:30:44,051
Come on.

720
00:30:44,051 --> 00:30:45,450
Come.

721
00:30:46,210 --> 00:30:47,650
Let me carry this.

722
00:30:49,051 --> 00:30:49,811
I'll take it.

723
00:30:49,811 --> 00:30:51,011
Let me.

724
00:30:51,011 --> 00:30:51,771
Careful.

725
00:30:51,771 --> 00:30:52,730
Give me that one. I'll carry that.

726
00:30:52,730 --> 00:30:53,730
Careful.

727
00:30:54,490 --> 00:30:55,690
Slow down.

728
00:30:55,690 --> 00:30:56,450
Watch it.

729
00:30:57,011 --> 00:30:58,490
Come. Slowly.

730
00:30:58,490 --> 00:31:04,051
Don't bump it.

731
00:31:05,091 --> 00:31:06,571
Put the big ones down first. Right.

732
00:31:07,571 --> 00:31:08,490
Here, have some water.

733
00:31:09,037 --> 00:31:11,237
♪Who would listen to
my sleepless nights♪

734
00:31:11,275 --> 00:31:14,162
♪Who cares about
the stars or the weather♪

735
00:31:14,162 --> 00:31:16,062
♪None of it has anything to do with me♪

736
00:31:16,112 --> 00:31:16,850
(Nuan and I will never be apart)

737
00:31:16,890 --> 00:31:18,291
We're leaving now.

738
00:31:18,291 --> 00:31:18,890
Alright.

739
00:31:18,890 --> 00:31:20,051
Take care.

740
00:31:20,051 --> 00:31:20,811
Slow down.

741
00:31:20,811 --> 00:31:21,531
Bye.

742
00:31:21,851 --> 00:31:22,771
Careful.

743
00:31:22,771 --> 00:31:24,650
Looks like you've found new friends.

744
00:31:25,611 --> 00:31:26,611
Seems like it.

745
00:31:26,662 --> 00:31:27,550
♪The moon has risen♪

746
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,851
I'll help them get settled first.

747
00:31:28,851 --> 00:31:29,650
Don't worry.

748
00:31:30,131 --> 00:31:30,930
Off we go.

749
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:32,455
♪The silence of the world
feels just right♪

750
00:31:32,531 --> 00:31:33,291
Get in the car.

751
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:34,011
The first one.

752
00:31:35,787 --> 00:31:37,475
♪Good night, world♪

753
00:31:37,475 --> 00:31:40,150
♪It's time for my own lonely celebration♪

754
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,400
♪A hopeless insomniac♪

755
00:31:41,450 --> 00:31:42,210
We might as well

756
00:31:42,210 --> 00:31:43,851
start a moving company tomorrow.

757
00:31:45,662 --> 00:31:47,212
♪Half drunk before I wake again♪

758
00:31:47,250 --> 00:31:48,250
Thanks for the hard work.

759
00:31:48,890 --> 00:31:50,131
It wasn't that hard.

760
00:31:50,771 --> 00:31:52,011
I'm just a little hungry.

761
00:31:52,170 --> 00:31:52,970
Hungry?

762
00:31:53,291 --> 00:31:54,811
Let's go grab something to eat.

763
00:31:55,210 --> 00:31:56,450
Who's paying?

764
00:31:56,531 --> 00:31:57,410
I'll treat.

765
00:31:57,450 --> 00:31:58,410
Sounds good to me.

766
00:31:58,851 --> 00:31:59,930
No expense claims allowed.

767
00:32:01,037 --> 00:32:02,325
♪Leave me with myself♪

768
00:32:02,475 --> 00:32:04,637
♪Just the noise, no more heartbreak♪

769
00:32:05,531 --> 00:32:06,331
Liangliang,

770
00:32:06,771 --> 00:32:09,210
several properties in Linwei Alley
have been transferred.

771
00:32:09,531 --> 00:32:10,851
You must make sure

772
00:32:11,091 --> 00:32:13,291
Lysen's acquisition goes through
without a hitch.

773
00:32:13,650 --> 00:32:14,930
I'll give it everything I've got.

774
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:16,051
Please don't worry.

775
00:32:16,371 --> 00:32:17,690
I've staked

776
00:32:17,851 --> 00:32:19,571
all my money on this.

777
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,890
There absolutely can't be any mistakes.

778
00:32:22,851 --> 00:32:23,851
Of course not.

779
00:32:24,531 --> 00:32:25,331
Good.

780
00:32:25,450 --> 00:32:27,210
Then I'll leave everything
in your hands,

781
00:32:27,210 --> 00:32:27,890
Liangliang.

782
00:32:28,771 --> 00:32:29,890
Bye, Mr. Rao.

783
00:32:37,490 --> 00:32:38,410
(Rao Yuci,)

784
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:40,450
(you probably never expected)

785
00:32:40,811 --> 00:32:43,051
(that it was your dad who helped me.)

786
00:32:43,730 --> 00:32:44,970
(Ever since you were little,)

787
00:32:45,131 --> 00:32:46,690
(you've always been the lucky one.)

788
00:32:47,051 --> 00:32:49,011
(Fate has always favored you.)

789
00:32:49,087 --> 00:32:49,687
(Five years earlier)

790
00:32:49,730 --> 00:32:50,811
(Five years earlier)
(But)

791
00:32:51,131 --> 00:32:52,450
(I've had nothing.)

792
00:32:52,771 --> 00:32:55,210
(I had to fight for everything
for myself.)

793
00:32:57,970 --> 00:32:59,371
You're dining with

794
00:32:59,371 --> 00:33:00,131
an important guest.

795
00:33:00,371 --> 00:33:02,291
Would it be convenient if I came along?

796
00:33:02,490 --> 00:33:03,851
Why wouldn't it be?

797
00:33:03,851 --> 00:33:05,170
My mom asked you to come.

798
00:33:06,771 --> 00:33:07,571
By the way,

799
00:33:07,571 --> 00:33:10,371
how's your thesis defense preparation
for the next couple of days?

800
00:33:11,131 --> 00:33:12,531
I still need to cut some parts.

801
00:33:12,531 --> 00:33:13,571
I feel like

802
00:33:14,571 --> 00:33:15,890
my argument has some problems.

803
00:33:16,531 --> 00:33:17,450
It's just

804
00:33:17,450 --> 00:33:19,371
analyzing some data.

805
00:33:19,531 --> 00:33:21,131
It's basically a formality for you.

806
00:33:21,131 --> 00:33:22,170
Don't be too nervous.

807
00:33:22,170 --> 00:33:23,091
I'm not nervous.

808
00:33:23,371 --> 00:33:24,331
Let's eat first.

809
00:33:24,930 --> 00:33:25,730
Mom.

810
00:33:25,930 --> 00:33:26,771
-Ms. Liu.
-Yuci.

811
00:33:27,291 --> 00:33:28,410
Liangliang, have a seat.

812
00:33:29,331 --> 00:33:30,210
Bai Liangliang

813
00:33:30,571 --> 00:33:32,131
is Yuci's good friend

814
00:33:32,131 --> 00:33:33,091
from university.

815
00:33:33,371 --> 00:33:34,611
This is Ms. Liu.

816
00:33:34,730 --> 00:33:36,410
A good friend of Mr. Rao's and mine.

817
00:33:37,331 --> 00:33:38,291
Hello, Ms. Liu.

818
00:33:38,291 --> 00:33:39,091
Hello.

819
00:33:39,331 --> 00:33:41,131
Yuci's friend is very pretty.

820
00:33:42,371 --> 00:33:43,490
Where's your family from?

821
00:33:44,371 --> 00:33:46,051
Her parents are diplomats.

822
00:33:46,371 --> 00:33:47,851
They've been working abroad for years.

823
00:33:48,010 --> 00:33:50,690
During the four years of university,
she has lived here by herself.

824
00:33:51,051 --> 00:33:52,011
Sometimes,

825
00:33:52,051 --> 00:33:53,291
she stays at our house too.

826
00:33:54,611 --> 00:33:55,650
Time flies.

827
00:33:55,650 --> 00:33:57,650
I thought it was just your parents.

828
00:33:57,650 --> 00:33:58,650
I didn't know either.

829
00:33:59,051 --> 00:34:00,331
Come on, let's start eating.

830
00:34:00,331 --> 00:34:01,890
Yes. Let's eat first.

831
00:34:02,011 --> 00:34:03,851
Liangliang, please have more.

832
00:34:07,070 --> 00:34:07,970
Thank you, Liangliang.

833
00:34:08,650 --> 00:34:10,370
Yuci, you're going to graduate.

834
00:34:10,370 --> 00:34:11,451
What are your plans?

835
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:15,330
I haven't decided yet,

836
00:34:15,330 --> 00:34:16,131
Ms. Liu.

837
00:34:16,850 --> 00:34:18,370
Why don't you come work at my bank?

838
00:34:18,700 --> 00:34:20,250
We're recruiting through
campus hiring right now.

839
00:34:20,290 --> 00:34:21,370
You should give it a try.

840
00:34:21,931 --> 00:34:23,451
Your parents

841
00:34:23,451 --> 00:34:24,290
would prefer you

842
00:34:24,290 --> 00:34:25,531
to find a stable job.

843
00:34:25,690 --> 00:34:26,411
Besides,

844
00:34:26,411 --> 00:34:27,931
jobs are hard to find these days.

845
00:34:27,931 --> 00:34:28,611
Right.

846
00:34:31,370 --> 00:34:33,411
The bank is great.

847
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:35,650
The benefits, the conditions,

848
00:34:35,810 --> 00:34:38,730
and the career development
are all very good.

849
00:34:40,810 --> 00:34:43,770
Liangliang, didn't you say before
that you were very interested in

850
00:34:43,770 --> 00:34:45,011
bank campus recruitment?

851
00:34:46,250 --> 00:34:47,051
Yeah.

852
00:34:47,250 --> 00:34:48,051
Right.

853
00:34:48,170 --> 00:34:49,451
Liangliang and Yuci

854
00:34:49,451 --> 00:34:50,531
are in the same major.

855
00:34:50,730 --> 00:34:52,091
Her grades are also very good.

856
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:52,971
How about this?

857
00:34:52,971 --> 00:34:54,411
You can both try applying

858
00:34:54,411 --> 00:34:55,770
to Ms. Liu's bank together.

859
00:34:56,611 --> 00:34:57,810
Please help them out.

860
00:34:57,810 --> 00:34:58,690
I'll appreciate that.

861
00:34:59,451 --> 00:35:01,210
Then I'll thank you in advance, Ms. Liu.

862
00:35:01,210 --> 00:35:02,270
We'll talk about it later.

863
00:35:02,491 --> 00:35:03,650
Let's eat first.

864
00:35:04,091 --> 00:35:05,210
We'll talk about that later.

865
00:35:05,210 --> 00:35:06,011
Right.

866
00:35:07,730 --> 00:35:08,370
You didn't even

867
00:35:08,370 --> 00:35:09,850
discuss it with me,

868
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,170
and suddenly suggested that the girl

869
00:35:11,170 --> 00:35:11,770
apply for

870
00:35:11,770 --> 00:35:13,091
my bank's campus recruitment.

871
00:35:14,891 --> 00:35:17,370
Youming, you saw

872
00:35:17,531 --> 00:35:18,810
how hesitant Yuci was.

873
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:20,210
I just thought

874
00:35:20,330 --> 00:35:21,411
if the two good friends

875
00:35:21,690 --> 00:35:22,531
could work

876
00:35:22,531 --> 00:35:24,051
in the same place,

877
00:35:24,451 --> 00:35:26,650
maybe Yuci would feel more comfortable
saying yes.

878
00:35:26,850 --> 00:35:27,850
So I...

879
00:35:28,770 --> 00:35:29,571
Zhaohe,

880
00:35:30,370 --> 00:35:31,611
you're thinking

881
00:35:31,690 --> 00:35:33,131
too simply.

882
00:35:34,051 --> 00:35:35,210
With my position,

883
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:36,770
I can only help Yuci.

884
00:35:37,850 --> 00:35:38,531
When we recruit,

885
00:35:38,531 --> 00:35:39,971
we don't just look at grades.

886
00:35:39,971 --> 00:35:41,170
We also consider

887
00:35:41,170 --> 00:35:42,850
many other factors.

888
00:35:43,650 --> 00:35:45,650
Liangliang told us about
her parents before.

889
00:35:45,650 --> 00:35:47,011
They have decent jobs.

890
00:35:47,131 --> 00:35:48,810
What does that have to do with me?

891
00:35:50,931 --> 00:35:51,730
Zhaohe,

892
00:35:52,011 --> 00:35:53,051
like what you said,

893
00:35:53,051 --> 00:35:54,210
her parents

894
00:35:54,210 --> 00:35:55,491
are already so successful.

895
00:35:55,850 --> 00:35:57,491
Why are you worrying about her?

896
00:36:15,091 --> 00:36:16,210
Miss, your receipt.

897
00:36:16,210 --> 00:36:16,971
Thank you.

898
00:36:18,850 --> 00:36:19,650
Liangliang,

899
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:21,131
I'm really sorry.

900
00:36:21,131 --> 00:36:22,931
Why did you pay the bill again?

901
00:36:23,131 --> 00:36:24,531
It's okay, Mrs. Rao.

902
00:36:24,611 --> 00:36:25,810
We're like family.

903
00:36:25,810 --> 00:36:27,210
It doesn't matter who pays.

904
00:36:27,451 --> 00:36:28,850
Well, I'm your elder.

905
00:36:29,250 --> 00:36:30,650
I feel really embarrassed.

906
00:36:30,650 --> 00:36:31,411
It's fine.

907
00:36:32,250 --> 00:36:34,290
Yuci, why are you just sitting here

908
00:36:34,290 --> 00:36:35,690
eating by yourself?

909
00:36:35,690 --> 00:36:37,051
You should learn from Liangliang.

910
00:36:37,051 --> 00:36:37,971
Look at her.

911
00:36:37,971 --> 00:36:39,411
She's very considerate.

912
00:36:39,411 --> 00:36:40,931
She paid the bill again.

913
00:36:40,931 --> 00:36:42,770
Yuci has always been protected
by all of us.

914
00:36:42,770 --> 00:36:44,770
She doesn't need to learn
those social tricks.

915
00:36:46,250 --> 00:36:47,131
By the way, Mrs. Rao,

916
00:36:47,370 --> 00:36:49,571
you mentioned
the campus recruitment earlier.

917
00:36:49,810 --> 00:36:52,451
I actually have my own plans.

918
00:36:54,330 --> 00:36:56,210
I'm not applying for that.

919
00:36:56,650 --> 00:36:59,290
I'm planning to apply for Professor Han's
graduate program.

920
00:36:59,770 --> 00:37:00,931
Thank you for your kind offer.

921
00:37:03,891 --> 00:37:05,571
A master's degree
in financial mathematics

922
00:37:05,931 --> 00:37:07,290
must be very hard to get into.

923
00:37:11,650 --> 00:37:13,451
I'm not like Yuci.

924
00:37:13,690 --> 00:37:16,240
I don't like following rules
or having my life arranged for me.

925
00:37:16,250 --> 00:37:18,370
I like to take control of my own life

926
00:37:18,370 --> 00:37:19,411
and my own future.

927
00:37:19,730 --> 00:37:20,850
For me,

928
00:37:21,250 --> 00:37:22,531
a stable job

929
00:37:23,011 --> 00:37:24,730
isn't important.

930
00:37:25,011 --> 00:37:25,770
Mrs. Rao,

931
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:27,850
didn't you also work hard
when you were young?

932
00:37:28,370 --> 00:37:30,531
Parents are just worried

933
00:37:30,931 --> 00:37:32,370
that we'll get hurt.

934
00:37:32,611 --> 00:37:33,531
But getting hurt

935
00:37:33,531 --> 00:37:35,210
is part of life.

936
00:37:35,810 --> 00:37:36,611
So,

937
00:37:37,091 --> 00:37:38,451
even though work is important,

938
00:37:38,531 --> 00:37:39,850
I hope to push myself harder

939
00:37:39,850 --> 00:37:41,170
and grow more

940
00:37:41,411 --> 00:37:42,690
during the best years

941
00:37:42,690 --> 00:37:43,531
of my life.

942
00:37:45,531 --> 00:37:47,411
Young people really are bold.

943
00:37:47,411 --> 00:37:49,451
We really are getting old.

944
00:37:49,451 --> 00:37:50,491
That's true.

945
00:37:50,730 --> 00:37:51,971
Liangliang

946
00:37:52,091 --> 00:37:53,531
really has her own ideas.

947
00:37:54,330 --> 00:37:55,650
Liangliang, I hope you don't mind.

948
00:37:55,850 --> 00:37:56,850
I didn't expect my mom

949
00:37:56,850 --> 00:37:57,931
to suddenly bring that up

950
00:37:57,931 --> 00:37:59,091
yesterday.

951
00:38:00,091 --> 00:38:01,650
Why would I?

952
00:38:01,850 --> 00:38:03,650
Your mom was just being concerned.

953
00:38:04,290 --> 00:38:05,091
Good to hear that.

954
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:06,290
Oh right.

955
00:38:06,290 --> 00:38:07,451
My mom

956
00:38:07,451 --> 00:38:08,491
really likes the duck.

957
00:38:08,571 --> 00:38:10,330
She asked where you bought it.

958
00:38:11,091 --> 00:38:13,290
I'll buy it for you.

959
00:38:13,531 --> 00:38:15,690
Don't worry about such small things.

960
00:38:15,810 --> 00:38:17,170
Alright. Bye.

961
00:38:17,170 --> 00:38:17,891
Bye.

962
00:38:20,525 --> 00:38:28,587
(Linwei Alley)

963
00:38:32,571 --> 00:38:33,370
(Linwei Alley Salted Duck)
One moment.

964
00:38:34,850 --> 00:38:35,810
Madam, the money's here.

965
00:38:35,810 --> 00:38:36,531
Alright.

966
00:38:43,011 --> 00:38:43,730
Thank you, madam.

967
00:38:43,730 --> 00:38:44,451
Please come again.

968
00:38:44,451 --> 00:38:45,091
Sure.

969
00:38:46,531 --> 00:38:48,170
Hello, half a duck or a whole one?

970
00:38:48,170 --> 00:38:48,971
A whole duck.

971
00:39:09,491 --> 00:39:10,290
Done.

972
00:39:10,531 --> 00:39:11,330
Here you go.

973
00:39:11,375 --> 00:39:14,612
(Linwei Alley Salted Duck)

974
00:39:14,650 --> 00:39:16,330
She didn't pay yet, right?

975
00:39:18,810 --> 00:39:19,931
That's my daughter.

976
00:39:29,350 --> 00:39:32,725
=Episode 8=
(Proof of Loyalty)

977
00:39:33,461 --> 00:39:35,901
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

978
00:39:35,901 --> 00:39:42,101
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

979
00:39:42,861 --> 00:39:46,061
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

980
00:39:46,061 --> 00:39:50,581
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

981
00:39:50,581 --> 00:39:58,101
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

982
00:39:58,101 --> 00:40:02,021
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

983
00:40:02,021 --> 00:40:06,061
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

984
00:40:06,061 --> 00:40:09,581
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

985
00:40:09,581 --> 00:40:13,541
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

986
00:40:13,541 --> 00:40:17,701
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

987
00:40:17,701 --> 00:40:21,901
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

988
00:40:21,901 --> 00:40:25,701
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

989
00:40:25,701 --> 00:40:29,781
♪Keep walking through the light♪

990
00:40:29,781 --> 00:40:33,981
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

991
00:40:33,981 --> 00:40:40,301
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

992
00:40:57,421 --> 00:41:04,061
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

993
00:41:04,061 --> 00:41:07,901
♪An apology that came too late♪

994
00:41:07,901 --> 00:41:12,541
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

995
00:41:12,621 --> 00:41:20,021
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

996
00:41:20,021 --> 00:41:24,101
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

997
00:41:24,101 --> 00:41:28,181
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

998
00:41:28,181 --> 00:41:32,181
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

999
00:41:32,181 --> 00:41:35,941
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

1000
00:41:35,941 --> 00:41:40,141
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

1001
00:41:40,141 --> 00:41:44,301
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

1002
00:41:44,301 --> 00:41:48,021
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

1003
00:41:48,021 --> 00:41:52,061
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

1004
00:41:52,061 --> 00:41:56,101
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

1005
00:41:56,101 --> 00:42:02,301
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
